  <title>Analytic Trigonometry</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      At this point we know how to calculate the values of functions at specials angles.
      For example,
      if we sail in the direction of the house of Manu Ko&#699;olau (NW), the angle is <m>45^{\circ}</m>.
      We can complete this triangle because we know the values of the right triangle for <m>45^{\circ}</m>.
      However, we do not know the exact value for the house of L&#257;
      (<m>22.5^{\circ}</m>).
      In this chapter,
      we will learn tools to help us further utilize the trigonometry in the previous chapters.
    </p>
